726502f-a.folder: Dry Harbor Road & Furmanville Avenue, Queens, NY
726502f-a.original_title: Queens: Dry Harbor Road - Furmanville Avenue
726502f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road (left not shown) west side, south of Furmanville Avenue, showing the old Methodist burying ground and site of the old Methodist meeting house of 1852. Most of the markers ave fallen, some are broken, a few of them remain s tanding. One reads Susanah Calyer died 1839, age 3 years. In the background the writer believes is 79th Place shoxing houses tbereon looking south from Furmanville Avenue. The cemetery property is now 1927, occupied by frame homes. One Burkhard owned it (ceaetery) in 1909.
Arril 1923.
Eumene L. Armbruster Collection

726515f-a.folder: Dry Harbor Road & 80th Street, Queens, NY
726515f-a.text:
Dry Harbor Road, west side, between 84th Street (left) and 80th Street (right) showing in three views an old house of which the following were the owners: - C. Westlake, 1852; F. Trippe, 1860; J. Treppe, 1873; and F. Kochesberger from 1891-1896. This
house does not appear in the 1929 Queens Atlas.
April 1923
Views 1,2 and 3
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection
